Let $\mathbf{M}$ be an $N\times N$ circulant matrix\index{circulant matrix!determinant}
with coefficients in an algebraically closed field $\mathbb{F}$,
and let $\omega\in\mathbb{F}$ be any primitive $N$th root of unity.
Then:

\vphantom{}

I. 
\begin{equation}
\det\mathbf{M}=\prod_{n=0}^{N-1}f_{\mathbf{M}}\left(\omega^{n}\right)\label{eq:Determinant of a Circulant Matrix}
\end{equation}

\vphantom{}

II. The\index{circulant matrix!eigenvalues} eigenvalues of $\mathbf{M}$
are $f_{\mathbf{M}}\left(\omega^{n}\right)$ for $n\in\left\{ 0,\ldots,N-1\right\} $.
